News Headlines 9th July 2026 
​🌍 Trump Declares Iran MoU "Over"
​At the NATO Summit in Ankara, President Trump officially declared the 14-point MoU & ceasefire with Iran dead. Following Iranian missile attacks on commercial tankers in the Strait of Hormuz, the U.S. launched 2 consecutive nights of heavy airstrikes targeting Iranian command networks, radar sites, & naval assets. In response, Iran fired drones & missiles at U.S. bases in Kuwait & Bahrain. Trump called dealing with Tehran "a waste of time" & warned of massive, rapid military escalation if attacks continue.  
​📉 Global Brent crude oil prices spiked nearly 8%, surging past $80 a barrel. Back home, the Pak Stock Exchange (PSX) plummeted by over 4,600 points. State officials warn that a prolonged conflict will aggressively inflate Pakistan's national oil import bill
​🇵🇰 ​Ocean rescue teams have successfully located the submerged wreckage of the K2 Airways Boeing 737 cargo plane in the Arabian Sea, 53 nautical miles off Ormara. The aircraft went down following a severe navigation system failure; search efforts are actively continuing for the 5 missing crew members.  
​Balochistan Operations: The ISPR confirmed that 54 terrorists were eliminated in recent high-intensity intelligence operations across Balochistan, though the country tragically lost 38 security personnel in the line of duty.
🔴​Finance Minister M.Aurangzeb announced that Pakistan is rolling out a brand new tax model driven entirely by artificial intelligence to digitize & reform national collections.
​🏏⚽ ​The ICC has charged the England & Wales Cricket Board (ECB) with breaching the anti-corruption code for airing dressing room video footage of Ben Stokes’ retirement speech during a live match tea interval, violating strict broadcasting safety protocols.
​Football Backlash: Defending champions Argentina advanced at the World Cup after a highly controversial penalty shootout victory over Egypt, triggering global fan outrage online over alleged referee bias
